node.text:
How to make a smooth, soft, pillowy meringue you can use on cake, pie or anything else you desire. It is cooked on the stove, so it is safe to eat without baking. But, feel free to use a blowtorch to toast it! 🔥♥️🤣 

Swiss Meringue Recipe from Zoë Bakes Cakes: www.zoebakes.com (search “Mile High Lime Meringue Tart”) 
Video edited by Henri: @culinaryunprofessional 
Music by my brother: @bluemusic82

Edited 4/17 - I just tried the recipe using a hand held mixer and after 10 minutes it still hasn’t become stiff enough to cover a cake. I will continue to experiment, but at the moment I suggest using a stand mixer if you have one.

node.title: Swiss Meringue from Zoë Bakes Cakes

node.text:
At a super young age I discovered baking brings me joy and feeds my soul. What I've learned from a career in professional kitchens is that I love teaching other people how to bake even more! Now I get to do both, on TV. @joannagaines and @chipgaines have given me a series on their new @magnolianetwork where I can bake, teach and be inspired by some phenomenally talented bakers (and chefs, farmers, bee keepers and more...) in my Minnesota community. 

This is a dream come true and on FRIDAY 2/5 you can watch the first full episode “Porch Party Pies” streaming on @discoveryplus. I’ll be making a lattice pie with strawberries and rhubarb (quintessentially MN and lovingly planted by my dad), plus a simple fruit “Fool” inspired by a trip to visit one of my favorite local pastry chefs, @pastrydiane. You’ll get a glimpse into my baking series (and my kitchen), where I break down all the secrets of pastry and share my tips and techniques.  It’s all crazy delicious and easy, so I hope you’ll tune in and bake along with me! 

♥️ Thank you @joannagaines @chipgaines @chefaz @in2itivecontent @producerweiland @p.mcmahill @madeleinenaomi and the rest of the many, many talented folks (there are dozens) who helped me make this dream come true. I also want to thank my family and friends who dove into this journey with me and made the show feel like home! It takes a village and you’re a spectacular one! #discoveryplus #magnolianetwork #zoebakes #minneapolis #baking #bakers #bake #tvshow #pastry #pastrychef

#ShareTheMicMN Trap or Grow, a five-track rap album and new music video by @appetiteforchange (AFC) Urban Youth, builds on the success of Grow Food. AFC youth wanted to continue sharing music that promotes and popularizes healthy eating and expand the message to encompass the opportunities for young people in North Minneapolis. 
 
You can either ‘trap,’ falling into the streets and the lifestyle that comes with it, or you can ‘grow,’ which means to grow your own food and build your own business. The young people wanted to create a movement encouraging one another to notice and question issues they experience and start creating their own solutions.
 
As youth activism is on the rise, teens feel more empowered than ever, we’ve tried to embrace that drive and encourage them to care about the food they put in their bodies, their community and their future. #kids #rapmusic #creating #urbangarden #growfood #mpls @standard_edition_women

Dorie and Devil's Food! There are a handful of people I credit for mentoring me throughout my career and @doriegreenspan is at the very top of that list. She is, to quote the @nytimes, "a culinary guru," but she is also a brilliant food writer, baker, cook, business woman and perhaps, even above that abbreviated list of culinary attributes, the most generous woman in the industry. But, if you follow her, you already knew that. She has graciously written about and shared my Devil's Food recipe in her latest bulletin (LINK IN MY @zoebakes BIO), where you will find the cake recipe from Zoë Bakes Cakes, along with my cream cheese icing and chocolate frosting (you can find my tutorial on the frosting in my IGTV). 

Her next, highly anticipated book, BAKING WITH DORIE comes out on October, 20th (available for preorder now ~ I'll put a link in my stories) and I have the greatest privilege of interviewing Dorie for the @smithsonian. It is a virtual event on Oct. 20th at 6:45pm, in collaboration with @politicsprose bookstore, you can get tickets now and you'll get a discount if you buy one of our books (or both💃🏻💃🏼). All of the event information is in Dorie's bulletin (LINK IN MY BIO). 

Just writing this post gives me so much joy (scroll to see the last time I got to see her at the @cherrybombe event). You can't imagine the honor I feel to have Dorie as a mentor and a friend. Please join us for the event and buy her book for all of your gift giving this season! You’ll thank me! ♥️

Apple Pie with stenciled whole wheat crust! Oh, I’m just getting started with the apple desserts. I promise chocolate is coming soon, but I love apples so much and the season is just getting up to speed. This crust is the same one you may have seen on Zoë Bakes (episode 1 @magnolianetwork), but I added whole wheat and rolled it with a stenciled rolling pin (scroll to see). That’s it! Almost feels like cheating, but the results are so fun, so who cares how you get there! You can find all kinds of patterns on these fun pins and create the pattern to fit your style and mood.

node.text:
Homemade Applesauce Galette! Simple, rustic and elegant. Sometimes less is more and in this case it is all about the apples. I rarely call out favorite desserts, but this is one of them; it is everything I love. Here in MN we have many apple varieties to choose from, although the season is just kicking off, so we’re not quite at full peak yet. I suggest you use a wide selection of apples when you make your applesauce. It results in better flavor and texture. Some apples are tart, some sweet, and combining them produces the perfect balance. The same is true for how they cook, some fall apart and create sauce and others keep their shape and add a really nice texture. I discuss my theory on peeling vs skins-on in the video, so check it out and you decide which way to go. I also put up a reel yesterday on making pink applesauce. And check out my latest “Extras” newsletter, where I feature Gretchen Perbix from @sweetlandorchard, you’ll find the link on my website, www.zoebakes.com. ♥️🍎🍏

Swirled Apple Tarte Tatin! In the midst of the recent news cycle I have baked a lot. Even my family has remarked on how many cakes, pies and loaves of bread have emerged from the oven and are stacking up on the counter. I bake for love, I bake to soothe my soul, I bake when I am happy or stressed. It is just what I do. I wrote these words many months ago and they are as true this week as they were back then. Life. 

As I scroll through instagram I am constantly inspired by other bakers, some at home and some in pastry shops around the world. This tarte tatin was inspired by William Lanagnère (@milkchef_off ), a pastry chef in Paris who took the rustic French classic and turned it into something beyond elegant. I marveled at the perfect spiral of apples and figured he had been paying much closer attention in the knife skills class than I did in culinary school! Then I realized there is a kitchen tool I don’t yet own; one that creates delicate ribbons of apple. I bought one (link in post) and in my VIDEO I'll show you how I created my version of this caramelized apple dessert at home. In my recipe I talk about what kind of apples to use, because that matters or you don’t get definition, just mush. 

RECIPE LINK IN MY @zoebakes BIO! VIDEO in my HIGHLIGHTS! ♥️🍏

Stay safe, be kind and be your best self. This too shall pass (a mantra that gets me through) and we will hopefully be stronger for it.  #tart #tarte #tartetatin #apple #appletart #caramel #pie #puffpastry #pastry #baking #pastrychef #comfortfood #frenchfood #frenchpastry #sparkjoydaily #zoebakes #dessert #recipeoftheday #paris #parisstyle #falldesserts #plated  #kitchentools

Fresh Bread baked three ways in the @EmileHenryUSA Wheat Stalk Epi Baker. It also has a lid, to cover the resting dough and it traps steam in the oven, creating a beautiful crust. I’m a big believer that equipment should do as many things as possible, so I tried the Epi baker with a traditional baguette dough, a very untraditional Sweet Cinnamon Roll and a non-yeasted corn bread. Scroll to see the beautiful results of each and I’m not done experimenting yet. The Burgundian clay absorbs and retains heat evenly for uniform baking, releases bread easily and will not chip, crack, craze or absorb odors or flavors. Designed for shaping, proofing, and baking in one vessel, plus you can use it as a server, since it’s so pretty!

node.text: Happy 30th Anniversary to my love, my life! 🥂🍾 Graham and I met in 1986 at a dance club in Burlington, VT. I was dancing, he was the DJ and he came onto the dance floor to ask me on a date. Five years later we got married on the most perfect summer day at his parents’ house on Lake Champlain. My mother’s best friend, Barbara, made our wedding cake (scroll to see). If you have my book, Zoë Bakes Cakes, you’ll know the story. She made that cake out of love and a sense of great adventure. Barbara wasn’t a professional baker, just a fabulous friend. We loved that cake so much then and even more now that I know what went into creating it. Everything from the food, flower arrangements and the vases at our wedding was homemade by our friends, family, Graham and myself. It was full of wabi sabi and felt just like home. Someone else DJ’d so we could dance all night and as you can see from the pictures I really threw myself into it! ♥️💃🏼🕺🏾🤣We’ve been dancing, eating cake and sometimes falling down ever since! Oh, with a whole lot of life and raising boys in the mix too. I can’t wait to see what the next 30 years brings, it’s always a homemade adventure! ♥️

node.text:
Figs. Pavlova. Firsts. The first time I ate a fresh fig was on my honeymoon. It was in the most romantic setting imaginable and to this day they remain one of my favorite foods. The figs were heavy with syrup and falling off the tree, which hung over the outdoor shower on a patio overlooking San-tropez in France. (As I write this it occurs to me that people have figured out to live in the South of France full time, while I shovel 5 feet of snow off my driveway in MN! 🤣🤷🏼‍♀️) We ate the figs off the tree, cooked them into jam, and cleaned them off our feet after stepping on them on the patio. By the end of our stay I was over them 😂🤣, but that didn’t last long. Just like rhubarb represents the end of a long winter, figs ushers in my favorite season, fall. The growing season is short, which makes them even more anticipated. If you’ve only had dried figs, this will be something special. Make sure they are heavy and soft and full of syrupy fig sugars. The hard, dry ones will disappoint. Purple or green both satisfy, but the purple ones are just sexier. 

This pavlova is full of boozy cherries and cream, which is a lovely compliment to the figs. I’ve baked this pavlova hundreds of times since 2018, stuffing them with Everything in season, and this combination is at the top of my favorites! 

You can find the PAVLOVA RECIPE in Zoë Bakes Cakes and on my website ZoeBakes.com LINK in my @zoebakes BIO! I also make it on an episode of Zoë Bakes on @magnolianetwork @discoveryplus! 

If you’ve baked my pavlova, what did you fill it with? If you haven’t yet, you’re in for a treat! ♥️

One of the greatest things about doing the show was having my boys join me (scroll to see them 😍 proud mom moment). They’ve been in the kitchen with me since I carried them into the restaurant in their car seats and propped them in a 60qt mixer while I baked for the lunch rush. True story! Charlie always loved to bake and even started his own scone company when he was 12 (more about that in the show), Henri came to it later (during the filming of the show 🤣), but he did and that’s a WIN for mom! You’ll notice my husband, Graham, is nowhere to be seen, which is exactly how he wanted it 😉, but was a constant support and taste tester throughout the show! (I hope he’ll change his mind for season 2 ~ hint, hint!)😂

This video was taken at the @bartenpumpkins farm where Henri and I learned about various pumpkins to bake with and got to pick (from the earth) which ones to take home. It was a gorgeous MN day and such a treat to get my 20-something son to do all the heavy lifting! 🤣😂🤣😂

Bread talk - “I promise you this is not weird!”🤣 Tomorrow my last two episodes of Zoë Bakes (season 1) launch on @magnolianetwork & @discoveryplus. Telling the stories of my food community and getting to share bits and pieces I’ve learned along my 30+ years of baking has been extraordinary! But, there are SOOOO many more stories to tell, so much more baking to do. If you enjoy watching the show, spread the Zoë Bakes love with your friends = season 2! 🎉💃🏼

Back to the Bread Talk! One of tomorrow’s episodes is about my friends at @bakersfieldflourandbread and baking fresh bread with my super easy @breadin5 method. Since 2005 Jeff and I have written SEVEN books in the Breadin5 series and sold nearly 1 million copies. That’s a lot of loaves baked in homes! We have combined the BEST recipes from all 7 books into one volume, BEST OF ARTISAN BREAD IN FIVE MINUTES A DAY! It’s available for preorder now, LINK IN MY BIO! 🍞🥐🥯🥖🥨🥪🍔 Happy Baking! ♥️
